external_knowledge:
- 'monetary seed' metaphorically refers to the 'amount' of financial commitments;
- 'financial endeavors' represents the financial transactions or commitments made by the department;
- The department's name 'Engineering' is the specific target of the query.

sql:
SELECT SUM(amount) AS total_home_loans_commitments
FROM commitments
WHERE type = 'mortgage loan';

SELECT department_name, COUNT(*) AS department_count
FROM departments
GROUP BY department_name;

SELECT jun_2004
FROM financial_data
WHERE id = 1;

SELECT fd.description, u.username
FROM financial_data fd
JOIN users u ON fd.user_id = u.user_id;
